According to Python documantation print funtcion has parameter end which defines characher print use in the end of the printed string, by defult it is &quot;\n&quot; (new line), so if we change it to &quot;&quot; we will be able to print letter of the word one by one. So last we need to do is to add small delay between prints. 

The solution:

```
import time


def print_with_delay(_str):
    for letter in _str:
        print(letter, end=&quot;&quot;)  # by default end in &quot;\n&quot;, instead I use &quot;&quot;
        time.sleep(0.5)


if __name__ == &quot;__main__&quot;:
    print_with_delay(&quot;Hello Friends!&quot;)
```

Hope it helped to solve your question.

